{{#is_alert}}

## What's happening?
JVM heap utilization on NiFi host {{host.name}} has exceeded 85% over the last 15 minutes.

Sustained high heap usage can lead to long GC pauses, flow stalls, or an OutOfMemoryError crash. Consider:
- Increasing the JVM heap size in `bootstrap.conf` (`java.arg.Xmx`)
- Reducing flow concurrency or disabling unnecessary processors
- Investigating processors with large FlowFile content in memory

{{/is_alert}}

